-- Fiat's Brand Chief Sistino Says Italian Car Sales Down About 19% in July
-- Tommaso Ebhardt
-- 2010-07-07T10:32:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-07/fiat-s-brand-chief-sistino-says-italian-car-sales-down-about-19-in-july.html

          
          
             Fiat brand Chief Executive Officer
Lorenzo Sistino said that Italian car sales are down about 19
percent in July, in line with June figures. He spoke to
reporters in Turin, Italy today.  
 “The trend is going in this direction due to the absence
of incentives,” Sistino said.  
          
          


  


        